 narrative way. Dominique Hipp captures, describes and analyses these self-positionings narratologically.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aConcentration campszGermany. 0aWar crime trialszGermany. 0aWar criminalszGermany. 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aAnklage. 4aDachau. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aEthik. 4aGerichtsprozess. 4aGewalt. 4aGnadengesuch. 4aJudith Butler. 4aKlaus Karl Schilling. 4aKonzentrationslager. 4aKreuzverhör. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMauthausen. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4aNeuengamme. 4aPerformativität. 4aQuellenkritik. 4aRavensbrück. 4aRecht. 4aZeitgeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aConcentration Camp.  aContemporary History.  aCross-examination.  aCultural History.  aDachau.  aEthics.  aJudith Butler.  aKlaus Karl Schilling.  aLaw.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMauthausen.  aMemory Culture.  aNational Socialism.  aNeuengamme.  aPerformativity.  aRavensbruck.  aViolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839450949zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839450949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839450949/original  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020